# t/research/skill-restart-safety.test — the SKILL harvest is crash-safe
# (decision-013), the skill sibling of the memory harvest's crash safety. A
# finished run's authored Agent Skill (out/skills/<name>/) is recovered even when
# store-skill never completes inline.
#
# agent-run-finished no longer emits store-skill as a Cmd — a crash between logging
# that message and the effect finishing would lose the skill forever (replay
# re-derives the Cmd but SUPPRESSES effects, and register-skill was never logged).
# Instead it records the run as a PENDING skill job on the tasks model. The
# harvest-reconcile subscription turns each pending job into store-skill; the effect
# ends by emitting mark-harvested{skill}, which clears the job. A crash mid-store
# leaves the job pending, and restart's replay rebuilds it so the source fires
# again. store-skill is idempotent (AddSkill upsert-by-name + register-skill
# upsert), so re-running the whole store is safe.
#
# This proves the FULL crash window: store-skill's AddSkill is faulted so the
# effect errors before emitting register-skill, the process crashes with the job
# still owed, and the restart recovers it. `fail content skill` targets AddSkill,
# the op UNIQUE to store-skill (its Files read is shared with capture-memory, its
# WriteSkills with agent provisioning) — so the memory and reply harvests are
# undisturbed.

send allow-sender { address kasi@decode.ee }

# --- Faulted run: store-skill's AddSkill fails before register-skill. ---
# No skills exist yet, so nothing is provisioned into this run at start — the
# provisioned box starts empty, isolating the skill the run authors.
fail content skill

deliver {
    from    kasi@decode.ee
    to      research@kasi.test
    subject "learn"
    body    "figure out how to pay invoices and remember it"
}
task 1 status is awaiting-agent

agent {
    out reply.txt                             "Learned it — saved a skill."
    out skills/pay-invoice/SKILL.md           [fixture skills/pay-invoice/SKILL.md]
    out skills/pay-invoice/scripts/extract.sh [fixture skills/pay-invoice/scripts/extract.sh]
}
task 1 status is awaiting-user

# The reply still sent — the skill harvest is orthogonal to delivery, and only the
# skill harvest was faulted.
outbound count is 1

# The skill did NOT land: the registry is empty...
model skills skills is ""
# ...and the run sits with a pending SKILL job, still owed a store. This is the
# crash window: the skill would be lost forever if HarvestPending were not logged.
model tasks harvest_pending matches "*skill*"
# ...and pay-invoice is NOT provisioned into the run's skills/ box — the whole store
# errored at AddSkill, before WriteSkills.
task 1 provisioned are ""

# The process dies and comes back: full-log replay rebuilds the pending skill job
# (the logged mark-harvested{memory,reply} clear those, but the skill job's never
# came), then the harvest-reconcile source re-fires — this time AddSkill succeeds.
crash
restart

task 1 status is awaiting-user                     # replay rebuilt the model
model skills skills matches "*pay-invoice*"         # the skill was recovered
task 1 provisioned are {pay-invoice/SKILL.md pay-invoice/scripts/extract.sh}
model tasks harvest_pending is ""                   # mark-harvested{skill} cleared it — exactly once
outbound count is 1                                 # no second reply — the reply job stayed cleared

# --- Negative control: no fault → the skill lands inline, registered at once. ---
# pay-invoice is now registered, so it provisions into this run at start; the run
# additionally authors billogram, which store-skill lands with no crash.
deliver {
    from    kasi@decode.ee
    to      research@kasi.test
    subject "learn billogram"
    body    "learn how to read Billogram invoices and remember it"
}
task 2 status is awaiting-agent

agent {
    out reply.txt                              "Saved it."
    out skills/billogram-invoice-ocr/SKILL.md  [fixture skills/billogram-invoice-ocr/SKILL.md]
}
task 2 status is awaiting-user

# The skill harvest completed inline: billogram is registered, and nothing is owed.
model skills skills matches "*billogram-invoice-ocr*"
model tasks harvest_pending is ""
outbound count is 2
